WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:18.143 --> 00:00:19.436 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Get a grip.

00:00:19.519 --> 00:00:20.729 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh?

00:00:21.896 --> 00:00:25.066 position:50% align:center
Day one and you're already
trying to get killed?

00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:26.860 position:50% align:center
Your turn!

00:00:26.943 --> 00:00:29.112 position:50% align:center
Here we go!

00:00:33.575 --> 00:00:36.870 position:50% align:center
[YUITO pants]

00:00:47.547 --> 00:00:49.591 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
You must go on living.

00:00:51.176 --> 00:00:53.303 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
I don't understand any of this.

00:01:01.269 --> 00:01:03.646 position:50% align:center
[WAKANA] You must never
allow the Red Strings

00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:05.690 position:50% align:center
to escape your grasp.

00:01:07.942 --> 00:01:11.029 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:11.112 --> 00:01:12.155 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:01:13.281 --> 00:01:14.407 position:50% align:center
Good morning.

00:01:14.491 --> 00:01:16.201 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]
Good Morning.

00:01:16.284 --> 00:01:18.620 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] It's supposed
to be a nice day today.

00:01:18.703 --> 00:01:21.956 position:50% align:center
We're off for a few hours,
so why don't we go out?

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:23.541 position:50% align:center
Let's get Baki charms!

00:01:23.625 --> 00:01:25.418 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:01:25.502 --> 00:01:27.962 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
See? Cute, aren't they?

00:01:29.547 --> 00:01:34.552 position:50% align:center
♪

00:03:01.222 --> 00:03:03.808 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER A]
MOA Others forecast.

00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:06.394 position:50% align:center
Suoh area, ten percent.

00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:09.064 position:50% align:center
Seiran area, fifteen percent.

00:03:09.147 --> 00:03:11.608 position:50% align:center
And twelve percent in Togetsu.

00:03:11.691 --> 00:03:14.486 position:50% align:center
The Extinction Belt
is near the stratosphere.

00:03:14.569 --> 00:03:17.864 position:50% align:center
There's no apparent effect on
the surface at this time,

00:03:17.947 --> 00:03:18.948 position:50% align:center
but please remain alert...

00:03:19.032 --> 00:03:20.408 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Hey, Nagi?

00:03:20.492 --> 00:03:22.369 position:50% align:center
I really think the soldier
who saved my life back then

00:03:22.452 --> 00:03:23.411 position:50% align:center
was Kasane.

00:03:23.495 --> 00:03:24.871 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
That's impossible.

00:03:24.954 --> 00:03:27.374 position:50% align:center
I mean, she is part of the OSF.

00:03:27.457 --> 00:03:29.918 position:50% align:center
She may have undergone
growth suppression.

00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:31.294 position:50% align:center
That's true.

00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:34.673 position:50% align:center
You can't tell an OSF member's
age based on looks.

00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:37.050 position:50% align:center
Take Captain Arashi
Spring, for example.

00:03:37.133 --> 00:03:40.178 position:50% align:center
Major General Fubuki Spring
is her younger brother.

00:03:42.472 --> 00:03:44.808 position:50% align:center
No need to worry about
formalities here,

00:03:44.891 --> 00:03:47.060 position:50% align:center
since none of that
stuff matters.

00:03:47.143 --> 00:03:48.770 position:50% align:center
Like Commander Seto said.

00:03:48.853 --> 00:03:52.148 position:50% align:center
Rank is nothing compared to a
person's ability, remember?

00:03:52.232 --> 00:03:53.525 position:50% align:center
--[YUITO] Hm...
--Still.

00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:55.944 position:50% align:center
We know for sure that Kasane
and Naomi are newbies,

00:03:56.027 --> 00:03:58.905 position:50% align:center
just like we are.
We're all 16.

00:03:58.988 --> 00:04:02.450 position:50% align:center
Ah, but I think I would
love Naomi no matter what,

00:04:02.534 --> 00:04:04.536 position:50% align:center
even if she was an older woman.

00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:13.169 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry for
dragging you along.

00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:15.130 position:50% align:center
Well, I couldn't let
you go out alone.

00:04:15.213 --> 00:04:17.549 position:50% align:center
Since you have a way
of attracting weirdos.

00:04:17.632 --> 00:04:18.591 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:25.515 position:50% align:center
Our brains have an
amazing power, right, kids?

00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:27.600 position:50% align:center
And we can use it to
connect to Psynet,

00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:30.228 position:50% align:center
which lets us do all
kinds of cool stuff!

00:04:30.311 --> 00:04:31.730 position:50% align:center
We can shop,

00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:35.400 position:50% align:center
[TEACHER]
search for information,

00:04:35.483 --> 00:04:38.194 position:50% align:center
send and receive messages,

00:04:38.278 --> 00:04:40.405 position:50% align:center
and some have a
much stronger power.

00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:43.033 position:50% align:center
It's a special talent
that's called psionics!

00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:45.452 position:50% align:center
They are... the OSF!

00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:49.622 position:50% align:center
[TEACHER, KIDS] The heroes
we call Scarlet Guardians!

00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:55.879 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
Yakumo Sumeragi,

00:04:55.962 --> 00:04:57.797 position:50% align:center
the founding father
of New Himuka,

00:04:57.881 --> 00:05:02.218 position:50% align:center
who saved all of humanity
in the Spring of Extinction.

00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:03.887 position:50% align:center
Must be cool to be you!

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:06.639 position:50% align:center
Your ancestor's grave
is a huge tourist trap!

00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:08.808 position:50% align:center
It's been 2,000 years, though.

00:05:08.892 --> 00:05:10.518 position:50% align:center
Feels unreal.

00:05:10.602 --> 00:05:12.187 position:50% align:center
Uh! Found it!

00:05:19.944 --> 00:05:22.530 position:50% align:center
They're doing Baki
crossover fortunes.

00:05:22.614 --> 00:05:25.200 position:50% align:center
The guy's dead, but he's
sure got good marketing.

00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:27.202 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
Yuito? Nagi?

00:05:27.285 --> 00:05:29.537 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI giggles]

00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:32.749 position:50% align:center
Hey, it's Naomi and Kasane!

00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:35.001 position:50% align:center
Did you guys come to
get fortunes, too?

00:05:35.085 --> 00:05:36.628 position:50% align:center
I'm just hanging with Yuito.

00:05:36.711 --> 00:05:39.714 position:50% align:center
And I brought Kasane.
What a fun coincidence!

00:05:39.798 --> 00:05:42.759 position:50% align:center
You must be a fan
of Baki, right, Yuito?

00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:44.135 position:50% align:center
Huh? Oh, yeah. I, uh--

00:05:44.219 --> 00:05:47.889 position:50% align:center
Here's an idea! After fortunes,
let's grab some tea!

00:05:47.972 --> 00:05:50.016 position:50% align:center
We've got time before
we start work!

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:53.645 position:50% align:center
Don't feel pressured, Sis.
It's a good thing I came along.

00:05:53.728 --> 00:05:55.522 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
Huh? Wh-What did I do?

00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:56.940 position:50% align:center
Kasane!

00:05:57.023 --> 00:05:58.566 position:50% align:center
[NAGI chuckles nervously]

00:05:58.650 --> 00:05:59.526 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
What?

00:05:59.609 --> 00:06:01.820 position:50% align:center
So, I've been meaning to ask.

00:06:01.903 --> 00:06:04.531 position:50% align:center
Do you two have an older sister,
by any chance?

00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:07.033 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] Mm. That's a
bizarre question, but no.

00:06:07.117 --> 00:06:08.618 position:50% align:center
Kasane's my only sibling.

00:06:08.702 --> 00:06:10.412 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] Any other close
relatives in the OSF?

00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:11.287 position:50% align:center
[NAGI chuckles nervously]

00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:13.415 position:50% align:center
Just us. Why are you asking?

00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:15.000 position:50% align:center
Enough about all that!

00:06:15.083 --> 00:06:16.918 position:50% align:center
Let's get our fortunes
and have some tea!

00:06:17.002 --> 00:06:18.128 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:06:27.137 --> 00:06:28.847 position:50% align:center
Aw...

00:06:28.930 --> 00:06:30.140 position:50% align:center
Tsk...

00:06:36.521 --> 00:06:37.939 position:50% align:center
How about you?

00:06:38.982 --> 00:06:41.317 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
Hm? "Great fortune!"

00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:44.404 position:50% align:center
So we all get "great
misfortune" except for her?

00:06:44.487 --> 00:06:46.698 position:50% align:center
At least one of us
can end up happy.

00:06:46.781 --> 00:06:50.827 position:50% align:center
I guess so, but it isn't a good
start to our career in the OSF.

00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:54.330 position:50% align:center
These fortunes suck!
Ugh, forget this!

00:06:58.835 --> 00:07:00.170 position:50% align:center
[gasps, grunts]

00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:01.671 position:50% align:center
Can't run from fate.

00:07:02.714 --> 00:07:04.591 position:50% align:center
Yuito! Cut it out!

00:07:04.674 --> 00:07:05.842 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Sorry, I had to.

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:09.179 position:50% align:center
One sec. I know what
to do with these.

00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:16.936 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
And... done!

00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:19.856 position:50% align:center
Maybe now, each one of us
can have a bit of good luck.

00:07:19.939 --> 00:07:21.149 position:50% align:center
Nice!

00:07:22.942 --> 00:07:26.363 position:50% align:center
Either way, let's give
it our best, alright?

00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:28.656 position:50% align:center
[NAGI whimpers]
Naomi!

00:07:28.740 --> 00:07:31.117 position:50% align:center
You really are a sweet person,
you know that?

00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:33.995 position:50% align:center
Forget about luck, your
kindness is all I need!

00:07:34.079 --> 00:07:35.997 position:50% align:center
You just saved my life
with that smile of yours!

00:07:36.081 --> 00:07:38.041 position:50% align:center
I've been truly blessed!

00:07:39.834 --> 00:07:42.128 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
The Seiran Regional Force?

00:07:42.212 --> 00:07:43.588 position:50% align:center
Where this time?

00:07:43.672 --> 00:07:46.466 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] Near Suoh Line Nine
in the old subway.

00:07:48.259 --> 00:07:50.762 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] They say they're
investigating Others again.

00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:54.474 position:50% align:center
So, no matter how
much we protest,

00:07:54.557 --> 00:07:56.976 position:50% align:center
it falls upon deaf ears.

00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:59.145 position:50% align:center
Increase our security.

00:07:59.229 --> 00:08:02.816 position:50% align:center
Right. Also, I received
an unverified tip.

00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:05.026 position:50% align:center
There's been unrest in Togetsu.

00:08:07.362 --> 00:08:09.948 position:50% align:center
I would assume that it's
those damn moon believers.

00:08:10.031 --> 00:08:12.534 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] I'll report back
once I know more.

00:08:12.617 --> 00:08:14.411 position:50% align:center
Please do.

00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:16.663 position:50% align:center
Now, Chief-- Kaito, rather.

00:08:16.746 --> 00:08:17.789 position:50% align:center
Sir?

00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:20.500 position:50% align:center
Yuito. How is he performing?

00:08:20.583 --> 00:08:24.045 position:50% align:center
I'm hearing reports that
he defeated an Other.

00:08:24.129 --> 00:08:27.132 position:50% align:center
We haven't spoken
since he was inducted.

00:08:27.215 --> 00:08:30.093 position:50% align:center
We may be brothers, but I don't
want it to appear as though

00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:32.679 position:50% align:center
he gets special treatment.

00:08:32.762 --> 00:08:36.224 position:50% align:center
I see... That makes sense.

00:08:36.307 --> 00:08:39.269 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] No further reports.
Take care, sir.

00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:43.356 position:50% align:center
[JOE exhales]

00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:51.948 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Seiran is making a move.

00:08:52.032 --> 00:08:54.492 position:50% align:center
Let them do as they please.

00:08:54.576 --> 00:08:55.785 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Hm?

00:09:01.833 --> 00:09:03.501 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:03.585 --> 00:09:04.794 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:09:08.840 --> 00:09:10.633 position:50% align:center
Wait... How did I?

00:09:10.717 --> 00:09:12.260 position:50% align:center
Something wrong, Yuito?

00:09:12.344 --> 00:09:14.512 position:50% align:center
Uh, it's nothing.

00:09:14.596 --> 00:09:15.805 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:16.848 --> 00:09:19.142 position:50% align:center
Alright, looks like
the gang's all here.

00:09:19.225 --> 00:09:21.895 position:50% align:center
It's time for a joint training
session so all you rookies

00:09:21.978 --> 00:09:24.773 position:50% align:center
can get in a little quality
practice time together!

00:09:24.856 --> 00:09:26.566 position:50% align:center
Like, all of us?

00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:27.984 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
Nothing too tricky.

00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:31.321 position:50% align:center
Just a mock battle for both
five-member divisions.

00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.239 position:50% align:center
The first team to claim
that flag in the middle

00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:35.241 position:50% align:center
will be crowned as the winner!

00:09:41.206 --> 00:09:44.167 position:50% align:center
Whoops! Kyoka Platoon
seems to be one short!

00:09:48.963 --> 00:09:50.674 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO gasps]
Arashi!

00:09:50.757 --> 00:09:52.801 position:50% align:center
Yeah, sorry. No can do.

00:09:52.884 --> 00:09:55.470 position:50% align:center
System software
is powering down.

00:09:56.971 --> 00:09:57.931 position:50% align:center
Then reboot!

00:09:58.014 --> 00:09:59.182 position:50% align:center
I gotta say,

00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:01.935 position:50% align:center
Arashi's kinda different
from how I imagined her.

00:10:02.018 --> 00:10:05.230 position:50% align:center
Yeah, like whenever you
see her on TV and stuff.

00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:07.941 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI] I'll give it a
hundred and ten percent!

00:10:08.024 --> 00:10:10.026 position:50% align:center
That's just for
promotional purposes.

00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:13.113 position:50% align:center
This is what she's like when
there aren't any cameras.

00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:15.990 position:50% align:center
The OSF calls her Lazy Ara.

00:10:16.074 --> 00:10:19.452 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI] Fine, fine.
Let's just get this over with.

00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:21.871 position:50% align:center
Now, then! Take your positions!

00:10:23.540 --> 00:10:24.958 position:50% align:center
Best of luck to you guys!

00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:26.710 position:50% align:center
Thanks!

00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:28.003 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:10:33.008 --> 00:10:34.884 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
Take a look, Kasane.

00:10:38.430 --> 00:10:40.056 position:50% align:center
--[NAOMI giggles]
--[KASANE gasps]

00:10:41.808 --> 00:10:45.020 position:50% align:center
When we wear these, everybody'll
know that we're sisters!

00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:53.111 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Sis.

00:10:53.194 --> 00:10:54.446 position:50% align:center
What's up?

00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:57.073 position:50% align:center
I'm curious. Have you been
thinking about Yuito?

00:10:57.157 --> 00:10:59.993 position:50% align:center
What? Kasane wh-what
do you mean?

00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:03.288 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:04.539 --> 00:11:07.500 position:50% align:center
It's not like an obsession...

00:11:07.584 --> 00:11:11.254 position:50% align:center
...but... I guess I
do kind of like him.

00:11:11.338 --> 00:11:13.006 position:50% align:center
--Understood.
--[NAOMI gasps]

00:11:13.089 --> 00:11:15.467 position:50% align:center
Then I'll have to do
some investigating.

00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:17.135 position:50% align:center
Find out if he's a good match.

00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:19.471 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI gasps] Wait, what are
you planning to do?

00:11:21.181 --> 00:11:25.310 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN] Huh. There's that
spoiled Sumeragi kid.

00:11:27.187 --> 00:11:29.564 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] He defeated an Other
in his very first battle.

00:11:29.647 --> 00:11:32.025 position:50% align:center
Don't write the kid off.
He's strong.

00:11:33.485 --> 00:11:34.277 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:34.361 --> 00:11:36.654 position:50% align:center
Now...

00:11:36.738 --> 00:11:38.907 position:50% align:center
...it's time to begin.

00:11:38.990 --> 00:11:41.368 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Ready, go!

00:11:41.451 --> 00:11:42.660 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN grunts]

00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:45.914 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN gasps]
Kasane!

00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:47.624 position:50% align:center
Watch out for fire, Shiden!

00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:50.251 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN, KASANE grunt]

00:11:50.335 --> 00:11:51.544 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:04.307 position:50% align:center
So, it's begun.

00:12:04.391 --> 00:12:06.893 position:50% align:center
Good luck! Do your best!

00:12:09.104 --> 00:12:10.689 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI pants]

00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:12.482 position:50% align:center
Sorry about this, Naomi!

00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:19.489 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:21.116 position:50% align:center
[NAGI, NAOMI grunt]

00:12:21.199 --> 00:12:22.701 position:50% align:center
[gasps, grunts]

00:12:22.784 --> 00:12:24.619 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI grunts]

00:12:24.703 --> 00:12:27.330 position:50% align:center
That trick again!
What is it called?

00:12:27.414 --> 00:12:29.624 position:50% align:center
I can see a split-second
into the future!

00:12:29.708 --> 00:12:32.502 position:50% align:center
My psionic power
is precognition!

00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:33.795 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:41.720 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI]
Ugh, what a drag.

00:12:41.803 --> 00:12:43.013 position:50% align:center
Found you.

00:12:45.557 --> 00:12:46.725 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:46.808 --> 00:12:48.268 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:12:48.351 --> 00:12:49.561 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:12:50.979 --> 00:12:52.814 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:12:56.234 --> 00:12:59.529 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO] Nice one, Gemma.
You've figured me out, have you?

00:12:59.612 --> 00:13:02.782 position:50% align:center
Don't hold back. Bring it on!

00:13:02.866 --> 00:13:05.702 position:50% align:center
[HANABI, SHIDEN grunting]

00:13:08.997 --> 00:13:10.206 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:13:12.167 --> 00:13:14.252 position:50% align:center
Alright. I'll head
straight for the flag!

00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:21.760 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:13:21.843 --> 00:13:23.053 position:50% align:center
Ha!

00:13:25.138 --> 00:13:28.516 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Hey! We're not
out for blood here!

00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:36.733 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:40.779 --> 00:13:41.905 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:44.949 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:13:45.784 --> 00:13:46.993 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh?

00:13:52.207 --> 00:13:54.000 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI grunts]

00:13:54.084 --> 00:13:56.127 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Uh... Arashi!

00:13:56.211 --> 00:13:57.921 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI]
Sorry, but I'm outta juice.

00:13:58.004 --> 00:14:00.632 position:50% align:center
I think that's more than
enough training for today.

00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:04.052 position:50% align:center
Nothing to be done, I guess.

00:14:04.135 --> 00:14:05.136 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA chuckles]

00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:06.262 position:50% align:center
You did great.

00:14:06.346 --> 00:14:08.890 position:50% align:center
So did you.

00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.266 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:14:12.477 --> 00:14:14.270 position:50% align:center
You weren't half bad out there.

00:14:14.354 --> 00:14:17.190 position:50% align:center
You did quite well in
our previous fight, too.

00:14:17.273 --> 00:14:18.775 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Uh, thank you.

00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.985 position:50% align:center
But, that doesn't
mean I approve.

00:14:21.069 --> 00:14:22.153 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Uh!

00:14:22.237 --> 00:14:23.655 position:50% align:center
I won't know whether
you're a good fit

00:14:23.738 --> 00:14:26.157 position:50% align:center
for my sister unless
I keep on digging.

00:14:26.241 --> 00:14:29.035 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh? Digging for what?

00:14:29.119 --> 00:14:31.871 position:50% align:center
--[phone rings]
--Sorry. I got a message.

00:14:33.498 --> 00:14:34.791 position:50% align:center
Father?

00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:36.042 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:14:36.126 --> 00:14:37.335 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Hm...

00:14:39.254 --> 00:14:41.506 position:50% align:center
Congratulations on
your induction.

00:14:41.589 --> 00:14:44.509 position:50% align:center
At first, I was against
you being part of OSF,

00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:48.096 position:50% align:center
but just see that
you don't get hurt.

00:14:48.179 --> 00:14:51.182 position:50% align:center
As such, now that you've
officially joined the force,

00:14:51.266 --> 00:14:54.144 position:50% align:center
I believe you're mature
enough to hear the truth,

00:14:54.227 --> 00:14:57.063 position:50% align:center
about our family and your
dear deceased mother.

00:14:58.732 --> 00:15:02.360 position:50% align:center
[JOE] I'll contact Kaito, and we
can all have dinner together.

00:15:02.444 --> 00:15:04.821 position:50% align:center
I'll be in touch soon.

00:15:04.904 --> 00:15:06.156 position:50% align:center
[YUITO sighs]

00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:10.702 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
Hm? 

00:15:10.785 --> 00:15:13.079 position:50% align:center
Kagero, what's up with you?

00:15:13.163 --> 00:15:15.457 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO] Hm? What d'you mean?
Something wrong?

00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:18.710 position:50% align:center
It's training.
Don't you... hate that?

00:15:18.793 --> 00:15:21.379 position:50% align:center
That I do, but we don't
get new recruits every day.

00:15:21.463 --> 00:15:23.631 position:50% align:center
And there's so many
girls this year!

00:15:23.715 --> 00:15:26.092 position:50% align:center
Gotta make a good impression,
now don't I?

00:15:26.176 --> 00:15:27.385 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Mm?

00:15:28.303 --> 00:15:32.974 position:50% align:center
[alarm blaring]

00:15:33.058 --> 00:15:35.852 position:50% align:center
Others sighted!
Sortie order is confirmed!

00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:39.814 position:50% align:center
In Suoh, near Line nine,
in the abandoned subway.

00:15:39.898 --> 00:15:42.776 position:50% align:center
Seto and Kyoka Platoons,
move out immediately!

00:15:46.988 --> 00:15:49.824 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA] The Extinction Belt is
at a low altitude right now.

00:15:49.908 --> 00:15:52.452 position:50% align:center
They'll be entering through
the ventilation system.

00:15:52.535 --> 00:15:54.162 position:50% align:center
[SETO] And the low
positioning means our comms

00:15:54.245 --> 00:15:56.581 position:50% align:center
might get disconnected.

00:15:56.664 --> 00:15:59.876 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] Telepathy without
braintalk functionality means

00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:03.129 position:50% align:center
that we'll only have one-way
communication from my end.

00:16:03.213 --> 00:16:06.758 position:50% align:center
[HARUKA] Let's hope that we have
working comms the entire time.

00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:09.260 position:50% align:center
Alright. Seto Platoon, move out!

00:16:09.344 --> 00:16:11.096 position:50% align:center
Kyoka Platoon, move out!

00:16:41.001 --> 00:16:43.044 position:50% align:center
Hey, we're brothers.

00:16:43.128 --> 00:16:45.213 position:50% align:center
You can tell me what
you've been up to.

00:16:45.296 --> 00:16:47.674 position:50% align:center
What's that look in your eye?

00:16:47.757 --> 00:16:50.093 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] I'm keeping
watch over this nation.

00:16:53.638 --> 00:16:54.848 position:50% align:center
[LUKA grunts]

00:16:56.057 --> 00:17:01.062 position:50% align:center
[footsteps]

00:17:10.155 --> 00:17:11.823 position:50% align:center
It's them!

00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:12.782 position:50% align:center
They're here!

00:17:12.866 --> 00:17:15.910 position:50% align:center
[footsteps, groaning]

00:17:19.205 --> 00:17:19.998 position:50% align:center
Separate!

00:17:20.081 --> 00:17:21.374 position:50% align:center
Now get ready!

00:17:35.847 --> 00:17:37.057 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS growl]

00:17:37.140 --> 00:17:38.850 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:17:38.933 --> 00:17:40.143 position:50% align:center
[HANABI, NAGI grunt]

00:17:42.771 --> 00:17:44.522 position:50% align:center
[HANABI grunts]

00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:48.026 position:50% align:center
Commander.

00:17:48.109 --> 00:17:49.944 position:50% align:center
Too much comms interference
from the Extinction Belt.

00:17:50.028 --> 00:17:52.655 position:50% align:center
If this keeps up, then we
won't be able to talk.

00:17:52.739 --> 00:17:56.034 position:50% align:center
[SETO] Wataru,
how's Kyoka Platoon? Hello?

00:17:57.118 --> 00:17:59.329 position:50% align:center
[HARUKA] Others have
been sighted! Evade now!

00:17:59.412 --> 00:18:00.955 position:50% align:center
Haruka! Can you repeat that?

00:18:01.039 --> 00:18:02.040 position:50% align:center
They're above our heads!

00:18:02.123 --> 00:18:03.249 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS growling]

00:18:03.333 --> 00:18:04.542 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Sis!

00:18:07.712 --> 00:18:09.589 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS growling]

00:18:09.673 --> 00:18:11.341 position:50% align:center
--[KYOKA grunts]
--[NAOMI] Commander Kyoka!

00:18:11.424 --> 00:18:12.884 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Arashi! Shiden!

00:18:22.811 --> 00:18:24.062 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:18:27.482 --> 00:18:30.026 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI gasps]
Yuito! Nagi!

00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:31.986 position:50% align:center
Over here, Naomi!

00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:34.197 position:50% align:center
[NAGI] So you're both okay!
What a relief!

00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:36.032 position:50% align:center
Hold on. Where's Seto?

00:18:36.116 --> 00:18:37.867 position:50% align:center
Our connection got cut off.

00:18:37.951 --> 00:18:41.037 position:50% align:center
But I'm sure they're okay,
all of them.

00:18:41.121 --> 00:18:42.539 position:50% align:center
Right, it would take
something far worse

00:18:42.622 --> 00:18:44.290 position:50% align:center
than this to bring down
Commander Kyoka.

00:18:44.374 --> 00:18:45.750 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Incoming!

00:18:47.210 --> 00:18:48.628 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
Look out, Naomi!

00:18:48.712 --> 00:18:50.255 position:50% align:center
--Nagi!
--No Sis!

00:18:53.258 --> 00:18:54.968 position:50% align:center
Gemma! Tsugumi!

00:18:56.803 --> 00:18:57.554 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:18:57.637 --> 00:19:01.766 position:50% align:center
[OTHER A growls]

00:19:04.185 --> 00:19:05.395 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:19:09.024 --> 00:19:10.442 position:50% align:center
[KASANE shouts]

00:19:15.447 --> 00:19:17.365 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:19:19.909 --> 00:19:21.119 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:19:29.252 --> 00:19:30.503 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:19:30.587 --> 00:19:31.796 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:19:34.591 --> 00:19:36.009 position:50% align:center
Is everybody okay?

00:19:38.261 --> 00:19:39.429 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts]

00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.723 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] We're fine here.
How about the other two?

00:19:41.806 --> 00:19:43.558 position:50% align:center
I don't know where they are!

00:19:43.641 --> 00:19:45.727 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Sis? Where are you?

00:19:48.313 --> 00:19:50.774 position:50% align:center
There! I can see them!

00:19:50.857 --> 00:19:52.359 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
Yuito! You're alive!

00:19:52.442 --> 00:19:54.736 position:50% align:center
Nagi! Where are you guys?

00:19:54.819 --> 00:19:56.654 position:50% align:center
We're on the other
side of the rubble.

00:19:56.738 --> 00:19:58.323 position:50% align:center
Naomi's with me, too.

00:19:58.406 --> 00:19:59.616 position:50% align:center
Wait.

00:20:02.744 --> 00:20:03.620 position:50% align:center
They're coming.

00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:05.872 position:50% align:center
Huh...? Tsk.

00:20:06.206 --> 00:20:08.291 position:50% align:center
--[NAGI gasps]
--What's wrong? Hey!

00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:10.502 position:50% align:center
--[NAGI] The Others!
--Naomi?

00:20:10.585 --> 00:20:13.254 position:50% align:center
Oh, no. Sounds like
it's a big group of them!

00:20:14.422 --> 00:20:15.632 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts]

00:20:18.885 --> 00:20:22.514 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:20:22.597 --> 00:20:24.974 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
The S-A-S cables!

00:20:25.058 --> 00:20:26.393 position:50% align:center
--[GEMMA grunts]
--Good plan!

00:20:26.476 --> 00:20:27.602 position:50% align:center
Go for it!

00:20:31.898 --> 00:20:36.903 position:50% align:center
[ALL grunting]

00:20:40.573 --> 00:20:41.991 position:50% align:center
[NAGI, NAOMI shout]

00:20:42.075 --> 00:20:43.284 position:50% align:center
Naomi!

00:20:46.996 --> 00:20:48.206 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:20:49.874 --> 00:20:51.543 position:50% align:center
Nagi! You alright?

00:20:51.626 --> 00:20:53.294 position:50% align:center
[NAGI]
I'll live.

00:20:53.378 --> 00:20:54.504 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Sis! Are you ok?

00:20:54.587 --> 00:20:56.339 position:50% align:center
I'm alright now, Kasane.

00:21:06.099 --> 00:21:07.392 position:50% align:center
Look out!

00:21:07.475 --> 00:21:12.147 position:50% align:center
[gunshot]

00:21:12.230 --> 00:21:13.565 position:50% align:center
[thudding]

00:21:18.528 --> 00:21:21.031 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI grunts, gasps]

00:21:24.409 --> 00:21:25.994 position:50% align:center
Wait, what just happened?

00:21:26.077 --> 00:21:28.455 position:50% align:center
Kasane, please, speak to me!

00:21:28.538 --> 00:21:30.540 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:21:30.623 --> 00:21:32.292 position:50% align:center
I'm okay. I just fell.

00:21:32.375 --> 00:21:33.710 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
What a relief!

00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:39.215 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:41.509 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:45.722 --> 00:21:47.474 position:50% align:center
What's wrong, Sis?

00:21:49.059 --> 00:21:50.769 position:50% align:center
Speak to me! Naomi!

00:21:50.852 --> 00:21:55.857 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI grunts, gasps]

00:21:59.069 --> 00:22:00.987 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:22:01.071 --> 00:22:04.032 position:50% align:center
No. Oh, please, no.

00:22:11.956 --> 00:22:13.291 position:50% align:center
Karen c'mon! Let's go!

00:22:13.375 --> 00:22:14.250 position:50% align:center
[KAREN grunts]

00:22:14.334 --> 00:22:19.339 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI grunts]

00:22:27.639 --> 00:22:32.644 position:50% align:center
♪